{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/css-variables","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"css-variables\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#css-variables\" aria-label=\"css variables permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>CSS Variables</h1>\n<p>Variables make our lives easy. For those not familiar with this word, a <strong>variable</strong> is simply a \"storage container\" whose value can change/vary, hence the name.</p>\n<p>In CSS, you can also use variables, or custom properties, an extremely powerful feature. But why even use variables in the first place? Well, for a very small website, it might not matter that much. But imaging you're using, let's say, a color more than once in your document, and you later decide to change that color. You'd have to go in every place that has that color and manually change it. This can get messy and confusing.</p>\n<p>With variables, you'd have to change the color in only one place, and it'll be updated everywhere where that variable is used.</p>\n<h4 id=\"global-declaration\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#global-declaration\" aria-label=\"global declaration permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Global Declaration</h4>\n<p>This makes the custom properties accessible throughout the document</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">:root</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--theme-color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> blue<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--default-font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 1rem<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>You can also define them within a ruleset, like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.article</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n   <span class=\"token property\">--font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 2rem<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"usage\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#usage\" aria-label=\"usage permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Usage</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">body</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n   <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">var</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>--default-font-size<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token selector\">button</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n   <span class=\"token property\">background-color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">var</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>--theme-color<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token selector\">.navbar</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>   \n   <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">var</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>--default-font-size<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>More on this topic <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Using_CSS_custom_properties\">here</a></p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"CSS Variables Variables make our lives easy. For those not familiar with this word, a variable is simply a \"storage container\" whose value…","frontmatter":{"title":"CSS Variables","date":"2020-10-26 17:27:18 +0100","categories":["other"],"tags":["CSS","Variables","CSS Variables"],"description":null,"keywords":"CSS, Variables, CSS Variables","author":"Rabson J Phiri","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAAPCAYAAADkmO9VAAAACXBIWXMAAAsTAAALEw